# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All Agents are linked to resources, applications, or tickets.
# - All ProductModels are linked to Organizations and Resources.
# - All Locations are linked to Sites and contain Resources.
# - All Resources are linked to Locations, ProductModels, Agents, Applications, and NetworkInterfaces.
# - All NetworkInterfaces are linked to Resources and NetworkLinks.
# - All NetworkLinks connect NetworkInterfaces and Resources.
# - All Applications are linked to Resources and ApplicationModules.
# - All ApplicationModules are linked to Applications and Agents.
# - All Services are linked to Applications/Resources.
# - All TroubleTickets are linked to Agents, Services/Applications/Resources, EventRecords, and Notes.
# - All ChangeRequests are linked to Agents, Services/Applications/Resources, and EventRecords.
# - All EventRecords are linked to ManagedObjects, ManagementSystems, and potentially Agents, and are part of Tickets/CRs.
# - All OperationPlans are linked to Pre/Post Conditions.
# - All Pre/Post Conditions are linked to OperationPlans.
# - All DocumentAttachments are linked to Tickets/CRs.

# The graph is dense and interconnected, covering various aspects of IT operations and incident management.
